<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title><%= title %></title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/main.css">
</head>
<body>
  <!-- Header -->
  <header id="header">
    <nav class="container" style="padding: 1.5rem 2rem; max-width: 1200px; margin: 0 auto; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center;">
      <a href="/" class="logo"><img src="/images/opencro-logo.png" alt="OpenCRO" style="height: 40px; display: flex; align-items: center;"></a>
      <ul class="nav-links">
        <li><a href="/#model">How it works</a></li>
        <li><a href="/#buy">Get FDA-ready</a></li>
        <li><a href="/#model-entry">Start with a model</a></li>
        <li><a href="/#about">About</a></li>
      </ul>
      <a href="/clear" class="cta-primary">Get FDA-Ready – $43K</a>
    </nav>
  </header>

  <main>
    <!-- Hero -->
    <section class="section hero-section">
      <div class="container">
        <h1 style="margin-top: 3rem;">Get FDA-Ready</h1>
        <p class="hero-subhead">Submission-ready cybersecurity. Fixed price. No rework.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Outcome -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>What you get</h2>
        <div class="two-column" style="margin-top: 2rem;">
          <div class="column">
            <h3>Submission-ready</h3>
            <p>Complete threat model with computed residual risk, as FDA expects.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="column">
            <h3>Outcomes not hours</h3>
            <p>Fixed price. We deliver what passes. No change orders, no surprises.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Deliverables -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>Deliverables</h2>
        <ul style="list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 2rem 0; font-size: 1.1rem; line-height: 2.2;">
          <li>— Complete system architecture documentation</li>
          <li>— Threat model with identified threats and vulnerabilities</li>
          <li>— Countermeasures mapped to each threat</li>
          <li>— Exploitability analysis with residual risk quantification</li>
          <li>— Supply chain threats analysis</li>
          <li>— FDA-compliant risk assessment</li>
          <li>— Evidence chain documentation</li>
          <li>— Quarterly audit for your product: exploit intelligence, regulatory updates, real-world incidents</li>
          <li>— One device (volume discount available for multiple device submissions)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- FDA Expectations -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>What FDA expects</h2>
        <p>FDA cybersecurity review focuses on whether you have:</p>
        <ul style="list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 2rem 0; font-size: 1.1rem; line-height: 2.2; color: #9CA3AF;">
          <li>— Clear understanding of your system architecture</li>
          <li>— Identified critical assets and data flows</li>
          <li>— Comprehensive threat analysis</li>
          <li>— Appropriate countermeasures for each threat</li>
          <li>— Quantified residual risk with justification</li>
          <li>— Evidence that controls actually work</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Process -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>The process</h2>
        <div style="padding: 2rem; background-color: rgba(107, 114, 128, 0.1); border: 1px solid rgba(107, 114, 128, 0.2); margin: 2rem 0;">
          <div style="margin-bottom: 2rem;">
            <h3 style="font-size: 1.25rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">1. Architecture Review</h3>
            <p class="text-gray">Deep dive into your system design, data flows, and critical interfaces.</p>
          </div>
          <div style="margin-bottom: 2rem;">
            <h3 style="font-size: 1.25rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">2. Threat Modeling</h3>
            <p class="text-gray">Identify threats against your assets and quantify exploitability.</p>
          </div>
          <div style="margin-bottom: 2rem;">
            <h3 style="font-size: 1.25rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">3. Countermeasure Mapping</h3>
            <p class="text-gray">Design controls tied to exploitability, not just compliance checklist.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 style="font-size: 1.25rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">4. FDA-Ready Documentation</h3>
            <p class="text-gray">Deliver submission-ready security documentation with evidence chain.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Price -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container text-center">
        <h2>Pricing</h2>
        <div style="margin: 3rem 0; font-size: 1.5rem;">
          <span style="color: #1E3A8A; font-weight: 700; font-size: 3rem;">$43K</span>
          <p class="text-gray" style="margin-top: 1rem;">Fixed price. Submission-ready. No rework.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container text-center">
        <h2>Ready to get FDA-ready?</h2>
        <p class="text-gray" style="margin-bottom: 2rem; font-size: 1.125rem;">Let's talk about your timeline and system</p>
        <a href="https://calendly.com" target="_blank" class="cta-primary" style="padding: 1rem 2rem; font-size: 1rem;">Schedule a call</a>
        <p class="text-gray" style="margin-top: 2rem;">Or <a href="/" style="color: #1E3A8A; text-decoration: none;">start with a Model</a> to see exactly where FDA will push</p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <script>
    const header = document.getElementById('header');
    window.addEventListener('scroll', () => {
      if (window.scrollY > 50) {
        header.classList.add('scrolled');
      } else {
        header.classList.remove('scrolled');
      }
    });
  </script>
</body>
</html>
